Merge pull request #117 from segmentio/retry Improve Retry Logic

Improve Retry Logic As outlined in https://paper.dropbox.com/doc/Analytics-library-guidelines-2trBhLKQD4Soz4VatvuGR#:uid=189560039280582553736180&h2=Handling-Network-Errors; our retry strategy should be:

1. Retry network errors (socket timed out, etc.)
2. Retry server errors (HTTP 5xx)
3. Do not retry client errors (HTTP 4xx)
  1. Except HTTP 429.

We had overlooked that Retrofit returns HTTP error as it's own type and this was not covered by the `NETWORK` error type. This patch fixes our retry logic so that we retry in case of HTTP 5xx errors and HTTP 429 errors.

Supply Retrofit log messages to log correct. (#96) Previously the raw retrofit message was being supplied as the "format"
argument to the log provided by the client.

This was problematic because this will caused most default
implementations of log to call String.format(msg), with potentially
unescapted "formatting" characters.

e.g. `analytics.enqueue(TrackMessage.builder("
Test").userId("1%5z90951"))` will fail the batch with this message:
retrofit.RetrofitError: Conversion = 'z'

because it String.format thinks %5z is formatting directive.

This change fixes it so that "%s" is passed as the format of the log
message, and the retrofit message is substituted in place.

Fix ISO 8601 formatting. (#92) Previously the library was incorrectly formatting Date objects for the
Segment API.

This was likely due to SimpleDateFormat's inability to understand the
ISO 8601 format "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssZ"
